# Advisorflow frontend – backend architecture

## This app (Frontend repo)

- **Stack**: React + TypeScript, Vite
- **Backend**: **Supabase** – direct client connection via `@supabase/supabase-js` (`services/supabaseClient.ts`)
- **No dependency on Nest/Express**: All data, auth, and real-time features go through Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, RLS, real-time).

## Nest backend (advisorflow-api)

- **Location**: `C:\Users\BharatS\advisorflow\backend\advisorflow-api`
- **When to use**: Only when we need **custom API endpoints** or server-side logic that Supabase can’t cover. Integrate then and call via `API_BASE_URL` in `constants.ts`.

Assume Supabase-first; do not suggest or wire the frontend to the Nest backend unless the task is explicitly to add or use custom backend APIs.
